pr_body:
Addresses https://github.com/bundler/gemstash/issues/107
Added two configuration options:
```
+      gem_path: nil,
+      storage_adapter: "Storage",
```

storage_adapter can be "Storage" or "S3".  If "S3" gem_path is the bucket in S3.

This is somewhat quick and dirty, so welcome feedback and support!

pr_title: Add backends for Gemstash storage of private gems
pr_body:
## Description
This pull request reflect the changes related to the GSoC project, "[Add backends for Gemstash storage of private gems](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/projects/#5922066392416256)".

## Blog Posts
1. [Introduction & Implementing Support for The ‘backend’ Property](https://medium.com/@gayashanbc/gsoc-2019-episode-1-introduction-implementing-support-for-the-backend-property-931b71f13f99)
2. [Implementing Trigger Function for AWS S3 Backend](https://medium.com/@gayashanbc/gsoc-2019-episode-2-implementing-trigger-function-for-aws-s3-backend-2f5c8b5eb7f7)

pr_body:
# Description:
Re-open previously closed PR.

With consideration of the past S3-related commits, I opened this pull request in order to work on it full time for this year's GSOC program. As of now, the work is not done, but I've created a mock S3 storage client based on the current storage implementation with all of the same methods, but with S3 implementation. This is so I could understand the concept of the task at hand, and make sure I'm heading towards the right direction.

The S3 class created is pretty much entirely functional. If you would like to run those RSpec tests, you can by providing your own credentials manually in the config.yml file located in the [~/.gemstash] directory. 

A functional S3 implementation for gemstash, which introduce the command flag -s3 to gemstash setup command. To run the gemstash module. 
```ruby
gemstash setup --redo --s3
```
Then provide the appropriate credentials.


______________

# Notes:
- Method `Gemstash::S3#delete_with_prefix` is not ideal, but is needed to clear the temporary files made for testing purposes.
- Working on new CLI test.

I will abide by the [code of conduct](https://github.com/gemstash/gemstash/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

pr_title: Gemstash Google Cloud Platform Backend Storage
pr_body:
# Description:
This is an unfinished work PR that includes an implementation of the storage backend utilizing Google Cloud Platform. It is based on the S3 storage implementation in #270, which hopefully will be merge before this one. 

`gemstash setup --redo --gcloud`

For now, it will be left unfinished until the S3 PR is merged and someone or (myself) picks this up and finish it.
______________

# Work to be done:

-  S3 PR needs to be merge
-  More detailed unit tests for the GCP storage.

I will abide by the [code of conduct](https://github.com/gemstash/gemstash/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

pr_body:
# Description:
Re-open previously closed PR.

With consideration of the past S3-related commits, I opened this pull request in order to work on it full time for this year's GSOC program. As of now, the work is not done, but I've created a mock S3 storage client based on the current storage implementation with all of the same methods, but with S3 implementation. This is so I could understand the concept of the task at hand, and make sure I'm heading towards the right direction.

The S3 class created is pretty much entirely functional. If you would like to run those RSpec tests, you can by providing your own credentials manually in the config.yml file located in the [~/.gemstash] directory. 

A functional S3 implementation for gemstash, which introduce the command flag -s3 to gemstash setup command. To run the gemstash module. 
```ruby
gemstash setup --redo --s3
```
Then provide the appropriate credentials.


______________

# Notes:
- Method `Gemstash::S3#delete_with_prefix` is not ideal, but is needed to clear the temporary files made for testing purposes.
- Working on new CLI test.

I will abide by the [code of conduct](https://github.com/gemstash/gemstash/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

pr_title: Gemstash Google Cloud Platform Backend Storage

# Description:
This is an unfinished work PR that includes an implementation of the storage backend utilizing Google Cloud Platform. It is based on the S3 storage implementation in #270, which hopefully will be merge before this one. 

`gemstash setup --redo --gcloud`

For now, it will be left unfinished until the S3 PR is merged and someone or (myself) picks this up and finish it.
______________

# Work to be done:

-  S3 PR needs to be merge
-  More detailed unit tests for the GCP storage.

I will abide by the [code of conduct](https://github.com/gemstash/gemstash/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

pr_body:
# Description:
A simple "quality of life" change to gemstash. 
If you type the command
```
gemstash info
```
It will return the current configurations settings of gemstash. This is useful because it was difficult to check what was changed in the gemstash configuration during setup. Let's say you decided to change to use memcached instead of memory caching, it was difficult to check what was in the current setup afterward. This command will allow you to do so.
In addition, it will be useful for #270 to check if the credentials were provided correctly.
______________

# Tasks:

-  Write tests for the command

I will abide by the [code of conduct](https://github.com/gemstash/gemstash/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).
